section.section:
If a medical record relates to a psychiatric or psychological problem and the attending health care provider, with any available and feasible input from a primary provider of mental health services, believes disclosure of any portion of the medical record to be injurious to the health of a patient or recipient, the health care provider may refuse to disclose that portion of the medical record to the patient, recipient, or person in interest but, on written request, shall:
Make a summary of the undisclosed portion of the medical record available to the patient, recipient, or person in interest;
Insert a copy of the summary in the medical record of the patient or recipient;
Permit examination and copying of the medical record by another health care provider who is authorized to treat the patient or recipient for the same condition as the health care provider denying the request; and
Inform the patient or recipient of the patient's or recipient's right to select another health care provider under this subsection.
